# ShitRat Slack Agent Monorepo Merge

## Decision

Move the live `shitrat-slack-agent` project into the ShitRat monorepo as `packages/slack-agent`.

## Why

The Slack bot is part of ShitRat's familiar surface, not a separate product. Keeping it in the monorepo makes shared identity/assets, future CLI wiring, and Slack deployment work local to the same system.

## Mention caveat

Slack `chat.postMessage` `username`/`icon_url` customization makes posts look like ShitRat, but does not create a mentionable `@ShitRat` identity. Reliable V1 summon should use `:shitrat:` reaction, with `:rat:` kept as an alias, until a real ShitRat Slack app/bot user exists.

## Receipt

- Copied the live Slack agent working tree into `packages/slack-agent`, excluding secrets, `node_modules`, build output, Wrangler state, and Pi session scratch.
- Merged Slack-agent Brain notes into the monorepo root `.brain/` and removed the package-local Brain copy.
- Scoped the package as `@joelhooks/shitrat-slack-agent`.
- Updated the monorepo README package map.
- Added `:shitrat:` summon defaults while keeping `:rat:` alias support.
